article.headline: Hampton 66, Norfolk State 60 (OT)
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Bruce Brown scored 16 points and Hampton's bench outscored Norfolk State's 32-2 Friday night in the Pirates' 66-60 victory in overtime. Hampton (15-12, 13-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) also got 13 points from Junior Pehoua and 11 points and 11 rebounds from Devin Green. The Pirates led by nine in the extra period until Norfolk State hit a late basket to create the final score. Norfolk State (13-13, 11-7) got 21 points from Tony Murphy and 12 points, 12 rebounds, five assists and seven steals from Chakowby Hicks. Hicks also had nine of the Spartans' 26 turnovers, which Hampton converted into 23 of its points.
